{"id":34603,"date":"2020-11-30T15:52:59","date_gmt":"2020-11-30T11:52:59","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=34603"},"modified":"2020-12-03T17:24:40","modified_gmt":"2020-12-03T13:24:40","slug":"ibn-masud-fear-allah","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/11\/30\/ibn-masud-fear-allah\/","title":{"rendered":"Ibn Mas\u2019ud on Taqwa: Sinful to show anger when told to fear Allah"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Zayd ibn Wahb reported: Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cIt is enough sin for a man to get angry when he is told to fear Allah.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source<span style=\"caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \"Droid Serif\", \"Helvetica Neue\", helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none\">: al-Mu\u2019jam al-Kabi\u0304r<\/span> 8588<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Rijal al-Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (narrators are reliable) according to Al-Haythami<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0632\u064e\u064a\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0647\u0652\u0628\u064d \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0646 \u0645\u0633\u0639\u0648\u062f \u0631\u0636\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0639\u0646\u0647 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0643\u064e\u0641\u064e\u0649 \u0628\u0650\u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u064e\u0631\u0652\u0621\u0650 \u0625\u0650\u062b\u0652\u0645\u064b\u0627 \u0625\u0650\u0630\u064e\u